# Levellio environment variables (EXAMPLE — copy to .env and fill in).
# NEVER commit real secrets. .env is git-ignored.
#
# Expo exposes only EXPO_PUBLIC_* vars to the client bundle. Treat anything
# here as publicly readable in the app; keep true secrets on a server.

# --- AI layer (pluggable) ---
# Levellio ships NO developer-funded AI key. AI is optional; the app is fully
# usable without it. Cloud AI uses the USER'S OWN key, entered at runtime and
# stored only in the device secure keychain (expo-secure-store) — never here,
# never committed. On-device AI needs no key and no network.

# --- Firebase (Community Projects: accounts + shared realtime backend) ---
# Powers the collaborative "Community Projects" feature (email/password accounts,
# shared progress, live activity feed) via Firebase Auth + Firestore. When these
# are EMPTY the app runs the feature in on-device "offline mode" (single-device,
# fully functional, no network) and lights up cross-device realtime once filled.
# These are NOT secrets — Firebase access is enforced by security rules
# (see firestore.rules), not by hiding the web config. Get them from the Firebase
# console → Project settings → "Your apps" (Web app).
# After filling these in: enable Email/Password auth + Firestore, then seed the
# featured projects with `node --import tsx scripts/seedProjects.ts`.
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
